cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with user profiling and similarity networks in the context of social networking services.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper involves natural language processing techniques for text messaging data.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses privacy-preserving measures for handling sensitive personal data.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as the paper proposes a privacy-preserving similarity measure for text messaging data.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper involves data comparison and similarity assessment.
